{"application": "software-mentions", "version": "0.8.0", "date": "2024-10-07T12:46+0000", "md5": "1A392830D188C7FC7CD93A2B54539683", "mentions": [{"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 7}, "context": "PyTorch code as possible. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0008724331855773926}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.33514404296875e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.1457672119140625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 7}, "context": "PyTorch provides basic optimizers such as SGD and Adam and torch-optimizer provides state-of-the art optimizers such as RAdam, Ranger or Yogi.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.4226646423339844e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.953975677490234e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid is built on the following principles:", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002849698066711426}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.8426368832588196}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid provides implementations of widely used masker networks: TasNet's stacked long short-term memory (LSTM) network [8], Conv-Tasnet's temporal convolutional network (with or without skip connections) [9], and the dual-path recurrent neural network (DPRNN) in [16]. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00013303756713867188}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003771781921386719}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid follows the encoder-masker-decoder approach, and provides various choices of filterbanks, masker networks, and loss functions.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.863739013671875e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.030632019042969e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid supports free filters [8,9], discrete Fourier transform (DFT) filters [19,21], analytic free filters [22], improved parameterized sinc filters [22,24] and the multi-phase Gammatone filterbank [23].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00018471479415893555}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 5.9723854064941406e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid supports several loss functions: mean squared error, scale-invariant signal-to-distortion ratio (SI-SDR) [9,29], scale-dependent SDR [29], signal-to-noise ratio (SNR), perceptual evaluation of speech quality (PESQ) [30], and affinity loss for deep clustering [6].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00024944543838500977}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 9.5367431640625e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid provides an optimized, versatile implementation of PIT losses.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.574920654296875e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.634252667427063}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid provides baseline recipes for the following datasets: wsj0-2mix and wsj0-3mix [6], WHAM [32], WHAMR [33], LibriMix [34] FUSS [35], Microsoft's Deep Noise Suppression challenge dataset (DNS) [36], SMS-WSJ [37], Kinect-WSJ [38], and MUSDB18 [39].", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.024547100067138672}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.2186508178710938e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid follows Kaldi-style recipes [45], which involve several stages as depicted in Fig. 2.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0021497011184692383}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00017648935317993164}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 0, "offsetEnd": 8}, "context": "Asteroid was designed such that writing new code is very simple and results can be quickly obtained.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.24249267578125e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9968768358230591}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "train.py", "normalizedForm": "train.py", "offsetStart": 4, "offsetEnd": 12}, "context": "and train.py, ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0017008185386657715}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.62396240234375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0017008185386657715}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.62396240234375e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 6, "offsetEnd": 14}, "context": "While Asteroid is not limited to a single task, single-channel source separation is currently its main focus.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012612342834472656}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0011413097381591797}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 9, "offsetEnd": 16}, "context": "Based on PyTorch, one of the most widely used dynamic neural network toolkits, Asteroid is meant to be user-friendly, easily extensible, to promote reproducible research, and to enable easy experimentation. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.933906555175781e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.28933823108673096}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 19, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "On all four tasks, Asteroid's recipes achieved better results than originally reported, by up to 2.6 dB.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997665286064148}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00026172399520874023}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "scripts", "normalizedForm": "scripts", "offsetStart": 20, "offsetEnd": 27}, "context": "We use the official scripts provided by the dataset's authors to generate the data, and optionally perform data augmentation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.8949598073959351}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0006734132766723633}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029904842376708984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 21, "offsetEnd": 29}, "context": "This paper describes Asteroid, the PyTorch-based audio source separation toolkit for researchers. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.291534423828125e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 21, "offsetEnd": 29}, "context": "This paper describes Asteroid (Audio source separation on Steroids), a new open-source toolkit for deep learning-based audio source separation and speech enhancement, designed for researchers and practitioners.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.076957702636719e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.999896764755249}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1801719665527344e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 22, "offsetEnd": 30}, "context": "This is what we do in Asteroid.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0002675652503967285}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.021763384342193604}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 26, "offsetEnd": 34}, "context": "Taking advantage of this, Asteroid provides PITLossWrapper, a simple yet powerful class that can efficiently turn any pairwise loss F or permutation-dependent loss L into a PIT loss.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.8252601623535156e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.007624685764312744}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "NumPy", "normalizedForm": "NumPy", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 40}, "context": "We also provide interfaces to NumPy [25] and torchaudio 2 . ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001977086067199707}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001812577247619629}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001977086067199707}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001812577247619629}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "pb bss eval 4", "normalizedForm": "pb bss eval 4", "offsetStart": 30, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "Evaluation is performed using pb bss eval 4 , a sub-toolkit of pb bss 5 [41] written for evaluation. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9958674907684326}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9802322387695312e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9958674907684326}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9802322387695312e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 31, "offsetEnd": 39}, "context": "To illustrate the potential of Asteroid, we compare the performance of state-of-the-art methods as reported in the corresponding papers with our implementation.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.42721325159072876}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.3870656490325928}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "model.py", "normalizedForm": "model.py", "offsetStart": 33, "offsetEnd": 41}, "context": "Instead of defining constants in model.py ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003679990768432617}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004801750183105469}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.003679990768432617}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004801750183105469}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 34, "offsetEnd": 42}, "context": "In this paper, we have introduced Asteroid, a new open-source audio source separation toolkit designed for researchers and practitioners.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 5.3048133850097656e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 35, "offsetEnd": 42}, "context": "This paper describes Asteroid, the PyTorch-based audio source separation toolkit for researchers.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 4.291534423828125e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "scripts", "normalizedForm": "scripts", "offsetStart": 36, "offsetEnd": 43}, "context": "Among the ones providing evaluation scripts, differences can often be found, e.g., discarding short utterances or splitting utterances in chunks and discarding the last one.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0001043081283569336}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.765655517578125e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029904842376708984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "FASST", "normalizedForm": "FASST", "offsetStart": 39, "offsetEnd": 47}, "context": "Classical open-source toolkits such as FASST [2], HARK [3], ManyEars [4] and openBliSSART [5] which are based on probabilistic modelling, non-negative matrix factorization, sound source localization and/or beamforming have been successful in the past decade. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "references": [{"label": "[3]", "normalizedForm": "[3]", "refKey": 1, "offsetStart": 906, "offsetEnd": 909}]}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 40, "offsetEnd": 48}, "context": "For training source separation systems, Asteroid offers a thin wrapper around PyTorch-Lightning [40] that seamlessly enables distributed training, experiment logging and more, without sacrificing flexibility.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.3484230041503906e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010194182395935059}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Source", "normalizedForm": "Source", "offsetStart": 45, "offsetEnd": 51}, "context": "These include nussl (Northwestern University Source Separation Library) [11], ONSSEN (An Open-source Speech Separation and Enhancement Library) [12], Open-Unmix [13], and countless isolated implementations replicating some important papers 1 .", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.00012373924255371094}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00016629695892333984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9950070381164551}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00016629695892333984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 54}, "context": "By showing experimental results obtained with Asteroid's recipes, we show that our implementations are at least on par with most results reported in reference papers.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.99764484167099}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.01931154727935791}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "DataLoader", "normalizedForm": "DataLoader", "offsetStart": 46, "offsetEnd": 56}, "context": "All the information required by the dataset's DataLoader such as filenames and paths, utterance lengths, speaker IDs, etc., is then gathered into text files under data/. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.5081018805503845}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.57763671875e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.5081018805503845}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 4.57763671875e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "scripts", "normalizedForm": "scripts", "offsetStart": 47, "offsetEnd": 54}, "context": "It is imported in both training and evaluation scripts. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.0003126859664916992}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029904842376708984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0029904842376708984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.9073486328125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 49, "offsetEnd": 56}, "context": "Regarding the optimizers, we also rely on native PyTorch and torch-optimizer 3 .", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9528728723526001}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00021797418594360352}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Source", "normalizedForm": "Source", "offsetStart": 50, "offsetEnd": 56}, "context": "[1] E. Vincent, T. Virtanen, and S. Gannot, Audio Source Separation and Speech Enhancement, 1st ed.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9950070381164551}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 6.80685043334961e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.5762786865234375e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9950070381164551}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.00016629695892333984}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 3.0994415283203125e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "HARK", "normalizedForm": "HARK", "offsetStart": 50, "offsetEnd": 57}, "context": "Classical open-source toolkits such as FASST [2], HARK [3], ManyEars [4] and openBliSSART [5] which are based on probabilistic modelling, non-negative matrix factorization, sound source localization and/or beamforming have been successful in the past decade. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 50, "offsetEnd": 58}, "context": "This paper describes the software architecture of Asteroid and its most important features. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 6.54458999633789e-05}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9996535778045654}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 5.960464477539062e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "conf.yml", "normalizedForm": "conf.yml", "offsetStart": 55, "offsetEnd": 63}, "context": "most of them are gathered in a YAML configuration file conf.yml. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.6317028999328613}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3470649719238281e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.6317028999328613}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 1.3470649719238281e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 56, "offsetEnd": 64}, "context": "Comparative experiments show that results obtained with Asteroid are competitive on several datasets and for several architectures. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 3.0159950256347656e-05}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 4.76837158203125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "ManyEars", "normalizedForm": "ManyEars", "offsetStart": 60, "offsetEnd": 72}, "context": "Classical open-source toolkits such as FASST [2], HARK [3], ManyEars [4] and openBliSSART [5] which are based on probabilistic modelling, non-negative matrix factorization, sound source localization and/or beamforming have been successful in the past decade. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 7.295608520507812e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0004222989082336426}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "pb bss 5", "normalizedForm": "pb bss 5", "offsetStart": 63, "offsetEnd": 76}, "context": "Evaluation is performed using pb bss eval 4 , a sub-toolkit of pb bss 5 [41] written for evaluation. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9958674907684326}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9802322387695312e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9958674907684326}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 2.9802322387695312e-06}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 75, "offsetEnd": 83}, "context": "We present the audio source separation framework in Section 2. We describe Asteroid's main features in Section 3 and their implementation in Section 4. We provide example experimental results in Section 5 and conclude in Section 6.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 0.02462083101272583}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9269475340843201}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 2.384185791015625e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999687671661377}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9999374151229858}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 6.258487701416016e-05}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "PyTorch", "normalizedForm": "PyTorch", "offsetStart": 78, "offsetEnd": 85}, "context": "For training source separation systems, Asteroid offers a thin wrapper around PyTorch-Lightning [40] that seamlessly enables distributed training, experiment logging and more, without sacrificing flexibility.", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 2.3484230041503906e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.0010194182395935059}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 1.1920928955078125e-07}}, "documentContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": true, "score": 0.991907000541687}, "created": {"value": true, "score": 0.9997989535331726}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 8.821487426757812e-06}}}, {"type": "software", "software-type": "software", "software-name": {"rawForm": "Asteroid", "normalizedForm": "Asteroid", "offsetStart": 79, "offsetEnd": 87}, "context": "Based on PyTorch, one of the most widely used dynamic neural network toolkits, Asteroid is meant to be user-friendly, easily extensible, to promote reproducible research, and to enable easy experimentation. ", "mentionContextAttributes": {"used": {"value": false, "score": 3.933906555175781e-05}, "created": {"value": false, "score": 0.2893381714820862}, "shared": {"value": false, "score": 